Money Stuff =0A Programming note=3F Several readers alerted me to the fact =
that last Thursday =0Anight=E2=80=99s episode of Elsbeth, on CBS, was about=
 (spoiler) a hedge =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=
=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12571501&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525=
&p=3D02102025>=0A=0A=0A=0AElsbeth=0A=0AProgramming note=3F Several readers =
alerted me to the fact that last Thursday =0Anight=E2=80=99s episode <> of =
Elsbeth, on CBS, was about (spoiler) a hedge fund manager =0Awho kills his =
identical twin brother out of sibling jealousy and also possibly =0Ato mani=
pulate the price of cobalt. It featured this dialogue:=0A=0AElsbeth (main c=
haracter who helps police solve murders): Hepson Capital took a =0Abig posi=
tion on cobalt the day before Bill died.=0A=0AFinancial TV anchor character=
