 reading about that, with Treasuries,=E2=80=9D =0ATrump told reporters Sund=
ay on Air Force One en route to the Super Bowl. It =0Awasn=E2=80=99t immedi=
ately clear whether he was talking about US government debt, or =0Apayments=
 processed through the Treasury Department.=0A=0A=E2=80=9CThat could be an =
interesting problem because it could be that a lot of those =0Athings don=
=E2=80=99t count,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CTherefore maybe we have less d=
ebt than we =0Athought of.=E2=80=9D=0A=0AOkay! Certainly one way to shrink =
the US national debt is to just decide that =0Asome of it doesn=E2=80=99t c=
ount. This is not an approach that gets mentioned a lot, or =0Athat has a t=
on of support among economists, but I have this sneaking suspicion =0Athat =
in like two months [6]  <> I am going to be reading tweets and op-eds =0Aex=
plaining thatof course a lot of US Treasury debt is fraudulent and doesn=E2=
=80=99t =0Aneed to be paid back, and that cancelling it will only make the =
economy =0Astronger. Anyway, maybe a good time to be a human rates trader.=
