entals of the Josh Allen MVP coin were =0Agood.=E2=80=9D But as far as I ca=
n tell,this coin <> is just a memecoin=3F Like there is =0Anot an event-con=
tract market where people take both sides and the contract pays =0Aoff $1 i=
f he wins and $0 if he loses. The coin has some vague correlation to =0Ahis=
 chances of winning, but that is purely psychological; there is no actual =
=0Apayoff from him winning. I once wrote <>: =E2=80=9CAll I am saying is th=
at if I sold =0Ayou a crypto token that was called =E2=80=98StripeCoin=E2=
=80=99 and I said =E2=80=98this is a token on =0Athe stock of Stripe=E2=80=
=99 you might say =E2=80=94 because you are reading Money Stuff, etc. =0A=
=E2=80=94 you might say =E2=80=98wait how is the value of the token linked =
to the value of =0AStripe=E2=80=99 and I would say =E2=80=98hahahaha it abs=
olutely isn=E2=80=99t.=E2=80=99 But my hypothesis is =0Athat not everyone i=
s as skeptical and literal-minded as you are, and some =0Apeople would just=
 go buy StripeCoin when they had nice thoughts about Stripe =0Aand sell Str=
ipeCoin when they had sad thoughts about Stripe and buy a whole lot =0Aof S=
tripeCoin when Stripe went public, and it would at least directionally end =
=0Aup being a sort of a proxy for Stripe stock. And everyone would get what=
 they =0Acame for, which is a convenient way to gamble on people=E2=80=99s =
feelings about =0AStripe.=E2=80=9D I think about this a lot.=0A=0A[3] Those=
 are the ones she calls out. Another possibly important one =E2=80=94 not =
=0Adiscussed in the statement, and not clear what the answer is =E2=80=94 i=
s whether =0A*investors* can sue for securities fraud.=0A=0A[4] That=E2=80=
=99s an exaggeration, and people talk a lot about (1) Bitcoin as a store =
=0Aof value and (2) stablecoins as payments infrastructure. But crypto as a=
 huge =0Achange in economic organization is less emphasized than it was in =
like 2020.=0A=0A[5] =E2=80=9CBitcoin is a good payment system=E2=80=9D is l=
ess emphasized these days. Also, =0A=E2=80=9CBitcoin is a good payments sys=
tem, therefore everyone has to hold a lot of it=E2=80=9D =0Aseems illogical=
, and you could imagine a payments system in which you turn your =0Aassets =
into Bitcoin only for a moment to pay for something and don=E2=80=99t need =
to =0Ahold a lot of it. (You don=E2=80=99t need to hold that many $1 bills,=
 either.) Also, as =0AI once wrote <>: =E2=80=9CA convenient currency for d=
igital cash transfer has a stable =0Avalue, and the rising value of Bitcoin=
